==English==

===Etymology===
{{wikipedia}}
First attested around 1925, from prison slang "stir".  See [http://www.word-detective.com/back-k.html], [http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=stir-crazy]. 

===Adjective===
'''[[stir]]-[[crazy]]'''
#{{idiom}} Of a [[prisoner]], mentally [[unbalanced]] due to prolonged [[incarceration]].
#By extension, [[restless]], [[uncomfortable]], or [[impatient]] due to [[inactivity]].
#:''After so many days of rain, the kids started to get a bit '''stir-crazy'''.''

